title: Brief Interruption, A - Radio Drama
description:
1 x 45 mins


For some time God has been meaning to speak directly to people and after some trial and error with various knobs he manages to break into BBC radio where he settles down with a cup of tea to try and resolve a few things. His train of thought is interrupted by faxes (which he must not answer, he must not get directly involved), but one of them catches his eye and before he knows it he is telling us about what happened to a little girl and her cat that she never let out of her sight
